a3mlnMaxPorts.name: a3mlnMaxPorts
a3mlnMaxPorts.description: The maximum number of virtual and physical ports supported by the agent. This value should be used to verify correct port values.

a3mlnMaxPhyPorts.name: a3mlnMaxPhyPorts
a3mlnMaxPhyPorts.description: The maximum number of physical ports supported by the agent. This value should be used to verify correct port values.

a3mlnCCSsaveErr.name: a3mlnCCSsaveErr
a3mlnCCSsaveErr.description: The count of detected CCS Parameter saves that failed during the previous set operation. A value other than zero indicates that the running and stored configurations are not the same.

a3mlnCCSdelErr.name: a3mlnCCSdelErr
a3mlnCCSdelErr.description: The count of detected CCS Parameter deletes that failed during the previous set operation. A value other than zero indicates that the running and stored configurations are not the same.

a3mlnSetStatus.name: a3mlnSetStatus
a3mlnSetStatus.description: The application's result of the last SET operation. This object is used to determine if the a3mlnLastSetMsg object is valid, and is NOT for general SNMP errors. In order to see warnings, this object must be polled after any set. The error state is communicated by the agent failing the set operation.

a3mlnSetMsg.name: a3mlnSetMsg
a3mlnSetMsg.description: The equalivent UI message for the previous SET operation. Valid only if a3mlnLastSetStatus is set to a value other than `setNoErr'.

a3mlnPortTable.name: a3mlnPortTable
a3mlnPortTable.description: A table of all physical and virtual ports which may be configured with the Logical Networks service.

a3mlnPortEntry.name: a3mlnPortEntry
a3mlnPortEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a physical or virtual port.

a3mlnPindex.name: a3mlnPindex
a3mlnPindex.description: This object specifies a port entry in the table and is specified as a value within the total port range (a3mlnMaxPorts).

a3mlnPtype.name: a3mlnPtype
a3mlnPtype.description: The port's type. A value of `ppmPort' indicates that the port has not been configured in any Logical Network.

a3mlnPowner.name: a3mlnPowner
a3mlnPowner.description: The port's owner (media type). If this is a Group Port, all Member ports must have the same owner. A value of `otherMedia' would imply a non-supported owner (media type).

a3mlnPlink.name: a3mlnPlink
a3mlnPlink.description: For a Group Port, this is either the value of the first member port or, if there are no member ports, the value negative two. For a Member port, this is the value of Group Port.

a3mlnPstState.name: a3mlnPstState
a3mlnPstState.description: The Spanning Tree state of this port. For a Group Port, this is the aggregate of all Member port states. If all Member ports are blocking, the Group Port is blocking. If a single Member port is forwarding, the Group Port is forwarding. For a Member port, this is that port's state. If the port has not been configured as an MLN port, the value `ignore' will be returned.

a3mlnPtbState.name: a3mlnPtbState
a3mlnPtbState.description: Only valid for Member ports. This is the Transparent Bridge CONTrol value setting of the learn parameter. If the port has not been configured as a Logical Network port, the value `ignore' will be returned.

a3mlnPgrpPrimaryPort.name: a3mlnPgrpPrimaryPort
a3mlnPgrpPrimaryPort.description: Only valid for Group Ports. This is the value of the physical port assigned as the group's primary port. This value is assigned by the agent and may change over time.

a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrPort.name: a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrPort
a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrPort.description: Only valid for Group Ports. This is the physical port used to assign the group's source MAC address used for all packets transmitted by the group. This value is assigned by the agent. A value of negative two indicates that no source port has been assigned or that this is not a Group Port.

a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrMedia.name: a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrMedia
a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrMedia.description: Only valid for Group Ports. This is the media type of the physical port being used for the group's source address. This value is assigned by the agent.

a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrValue.name: a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrValue
a3mlnPgrpSrcAdrValue.description: Only valid for Group Ports. This is the physical MAC address of the group's source port. In the future, a profile VARIATION should be used to further specify media formats such as MacAddress, SMDSAddress, etc. This value is assigned by the agent.

a3mlnPgrpDescription.name: a3mlnPgrpDescription
a3mlnPgrpDescription.description: Only valid for Group Ports. This is the description (name) string for this Logical Network.

a3mlnGroupTable.name: a3mlnGroupTable
a3mlnGroupTable.description: A table of all configured Logical Network Group Ports.

a3mlnGroupEntry.name: a3mlnGroupEntry
a3mlnGroupEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a Logical Network's Group Port.

a3mlnGrpPort.name: a3mlnGrpPort
a3mlnGrpPort.description: This object specifies an entry in the table, and is a Group Port. Group Ports are virtual ports used as points of attachment to Logical Networks by upper layer clients. Valid values number within the virtual port range (greater than a3mlnMaxPhyPorts and less than a3mlnMaxPorts).

a3mlnGrpPortType.name: a3mlnGrpPortType
a3mlnGrpPortType.description: This port's type. The only valid value for a Group Port is `groupPort'.

a3mlnGrpPortState.name: a3mlnGrpPortState
a3mlnGrpPortState.description: The PPM state of this Group Port.

a3mlnGrpPrimaryPort.name: a3mlnGrpPrimaryPort
a3mlnGrpPrimaryPort.description: This is the value of the physical port assigned as the group's primary port. This value is assigned by the agent.

a3mlnGrpOwner.name: a3mlnGrpOwner
a3mlnGrpOwner.description: The owner of this group (which is actually the media type for the group). All Member ports must have the same owner.

a3mlnGrpMemberCount.name: a3mlnGrpMemberCount
a3mlnGrpMemberCount.description: The number of Member ports in this group.

a3mlnGrpFirstMember.name: a3mlnGrpFirstMember
a3mlnGrpFirstMember.description: This is the value (index) of the first Member port of this group. A value of negative two indicates that no Member ports have been configured.

a3mlnGrpDescription.name: a3mlnGrpDescription
a3mlnGrpDescription.description: The description (name) string for this logical network.

a3mlnGrpEntryStatus.name: a3mlnGrpEntryStatus
a3mlnGrpEntryStatus.description: This object is used to add and delete entries in this table. See RowStatus description at the beginning of this MIB. Note - A group's description may be changed without first deleting the row.

a3mlnMemberTable.name: a3mlnMemberTable
a3mlnMemberTable.description: A table of configured Logical Networks.

a3mlnMemberEntry.name: a3mlnMemberEntry
a3mlnMemberEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a Logical Network.

a3mlnMemGrpPort.name: a3mlnMemGrpPort
a3mlnMemGrpPort.description: This object specifies a Logical Network within the table and is a Group Port within the virtual port range (greater than a3mlnMaxPhyPorts and less than a3mlnMaxPorts).

a3mlnMemPort.name: a3mlnMemPort
a3mlnMemPort.description: This object specifies a Member port within a Logical Network and is a physical port within the physical port range (less than a3mlnMaxPhyPorts).

a3mlnMemOwner.name: a3mlnMemOwner
a3mlnMemOwner.description: The owner of this group (which is actually the media type for the group). All Member ports must have the same owner.

a3mlnMemEntryStatus.name: a3mlnMemEntryStatus
a3mlnMemEntryStatus.description: This object is used to add and delete entries in this table. See RowStatus description at the beginning of this MIB.

a3mlnStatSelGrpPort.name: a3mlnStatSelGrpPort
a3mlnStatSelGrpPort.description: The number of times a Group Port has been selected.

a3mlnStatSelMacAdr.name: a3mlnStatSelMacAdr
a3mlnStatSelMacAdr.description: The number of times a MAC address has been selected.

a3mlnPortStatTable.name: a3mlnPortStatTable
a3mlnPortStatTable.description: A table of Logical Network Member port statistics.

a3mlnPortStatEntry.name: a3mlnPortStatEntry
a3mlnPortStatEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents statistics for a Member port of a Logical Network.

a3mlnPStatIndex.name: a3mlnPStatIndex
a3mlnPStatIndex.description: This object specifies an entry in the port statistics table and is a Member port within the physical port range (less than a3mlnMaxPhyPorts).

a3mlnPStatRcvd.name: a3mlnPStatRcvd
a3mlnPStatRcvd.description: Count of data frames received on this port.

a3mlnPStatXmit.name: a3mlnPStatXmit
a3mlnPStatXmit.description: Count of data frames transmitted from this port.

a3mlnPStatStaMoveFrom.name: a3mlnPStatStaMoveFrom
a3mlnPStatStaMoveFrom.description: Count of detected stations moving away from this port.

a3mlnPStatStaMoveTo.name: a3mlnPStatStaMoveTo
a3mlnPStatStaMoveTo.description: Count of detected stations moving to this port.

a3mlnPStatSTAchange.name: a3mlnPStatSTAchange
a3mlnPStatSTAchange.description: Count of Spanning Tree state changes for this port.
